Events[edit]

March[edit]

  • 29 – The 23rd Vossajazz started in Voss, Norway (March 29 – 31).[1]

May[edit]

  • 22 – The 24th Nattjazz started in Bergen, Norway (May 22 – June 2).[2]

June[edit]

  • 15 – The Norwegian Wood started in Oslo, Norway (June 15 – 16).[3]
  • 29 – The 27th Kalvøyafestivalen started at Kalvøya near by Oslo (June 29 – 30).[4]

July[edit]

  • 15 – The 36th Moldejazz started in Molde, Norway (July 15 – 20).[5]

Albums released[edit]

March
  • 25 – Visible World (ECM Records), by Jan Garbarek[6]

K

Karin Krog
  • Huskonsert I Aurskog – Musikk Av Og Etter Anders Heyerdahl (Meantime Records)[7]

Deaths[edit]

March
  • 14 – Maj Sønstevold, composer, pianist, and music teacher (born 1917).[8]
June
  • 5 – Anne-Marie Ørbeck, classical pianist and composer (born 1911).[9]
October
  • 9 – Per Asplin, pianist, singer, composer and actor (born 1928).[10]
  • 29 – Robert Levin, classical pianist and composer (born 1912).[11]
November
  • 5 – Arne Hendriksen, operatic tenor (born 1911).[12]

Births[edit]

January
  • 29 – Nora Foss al-Jabri, singer.
June
  • 15 – Aurora (Aksnes), singer and songwriter.
September
  • 5 – Sigrid (Solbakk Raab), singer and songwriter.
October
  • 12 – Astrid S(meplass), singer and songwriter.
November
  • 4 – Adelén (Rusillo Steen), singer.
